gov.va.isaac.interfaces.gui.views.commonFunctionality

Interface XMLViewI

  • All Superinterfaces:
    IsaacViewI, PopupViewI
    All Known Implementing Classes:
    XMLDisplayWindow

    @Contract
public interface XMLViewI
extends PopupViewI
    XMLViewI Extends the IsaacViewI to provide a View which will pop up a new window on top of the parent window when the showView method is called. Implementations are intended to simply display the specified XML in a window.
    Author:
    Dan Armbrust

    • Method Detail

      • setParameters

        void setParameters(String title,
                   Supplier<String> xmlContent,
                   int width,
                   int height)
        Display this popup view to the user in front of the specified parent window. The PopupViewI implementation is responsible for showing itself when this method is called. The content is passed in via the Supplier interface, so that if gathering the XML is expensive, good implementations can background thread this job.
